Every Device in the network are generate logs for acvtivties performed on it 
Some common devices are found on the network are genrete logs  

1- Event Viwer  
  logs every events perfrom on the windows 
  it is assign uniqu id for every  log or activty
  the logs are in the event viwer are forwarded to SIEM 
2- Linux work station 
     some logs genreated in linux:
     /var/log/httpd : Contains HTTP Request  / Response and error logs.
    /var/log/cron   : Events related to cron jobs are stored in this location.
    /var/log/auth.log and /var/log/secure : Stores authentication related logs.
    /var/log/kern : This file stores kernel related events.
    
3- Web server 
   logs are stored in linux /var/log/apache or /var/log/httpd.


Log ingestion
each logs provide a rich info about security info 
Every SIEM has way to  ingerstion these logs  
here is some methodes how SEIM indestion these logs  

1- Agent/Forwarder 
   it si tool installed on the endpoint it is configured to collect logs on the endpoint 
2- syslog 
   it is network protcol used to collect logs from devices 
3-  Manul Upload  
     allow users to ingest offline data for quick analysis. Once the data is ingested, it is normalized and made available for analysis.
4- port forwared  
   SIEM listen on certain port  and endpoint forwared the logs or data from SIEM 
   
